'Vasilyev' (Васильев) or 'Vasiliev' or 'Vassiliev' is a common Russian Surname
derived from the Russian given name Vasiliy (equivalent of Basil). The feminine
form: 'Vasilyeva' ('Vasilieva'). It may refer to: *Aleksandr Vasilev (b. 1969),
